<div id="subtree-container" class="subtree-container"><div class="aea2d7dde423afa7ad9351a0886150a8-scss b51b00c1669ad99a1c607cd1e77c2824-scss" style="inset: 0px 269px 642px 0px; justify-content: flex-end;"><div class="afeebf1df237d4103108ba40799802d6-scss b174ef864cda601f37d52e9ca06b1dc7-scss"><div class="c13443431e58facf06f9d12490b92a82-scss" style="width: 90vw; max-width: 8.5in;"><div class="_0df5ec6b9902d7d22ccfa3ebb4f35211-scss">Equipments and Fixtures</div><div class="e5e059a27f4c194020f0d961a3cb5989-scss" dir="auto"><div class="fr-view"><p>The quantification methods for equipment and fixtures can vary according to the available information:</p>
<ul>
<li>If the items <strong>are modeled</strong>, they should be <strong>quantified by type and specification</strong>. The measurement unit may vary based on the nature of the element, such as:<ul>
<li>Count: pumps, valves, drains, etc.</li>
<li>Meters/Feet: gutters and other linear elements.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>If the items are <strong>not modeled</strong>, they should be <strong>included in a total sum</strong>, clearly described and specified within the corresponding Bill of Quantities (BoQ) item.</li>
</ul></div></div></div></div></div></div>